# Sharon Wairimu Portfolio

## Overview
![Portfolio Screenshot](./images/screenshot.png)

A responsive portfolio website showcasing Sharon Wairimu's expertise in microbiology and culinary arts. The site features a clean design with sections for professional background, research work, and recipe collections.

## Features

### Microbiology Portfolio
- Professional background and education
- Research projects and publications
- Laboratory skills and specialties
- Academic achievements

### Culinary Portfolio
- Recipe collection hub
- Detailed chicken recipes
- Fried rice variations
- Cooking techniques

### Technical Features
- Fully responsive design
- Semantic HTML5 structure
- Clean CSS styling
- Easy-to-navigate layout
- Fast loading performance

## Technologies Used

- **Frontend**:
  - HTML5
  - CSS3 (Flexbox/Grid)
  - Responsive Web Design

- **Development Tools**:
  - Visual Studio Code
  - Git/GitHub
  - Chrome DevTools

## Project Structure

```
sharon-portfolio/
├── index.html          # Homepage
├── about.html          # Professional background
├── research.html       # Scientific work
├── menu.html           # Recipe hub
├── recipe.html         # Chicken recipes
├── recipe2.html        # Fried rice recipes
├── style.css           # Main stylesheet
├── images/             # All assets
│   ├── profile.jpg
│   ├── lab-work.jpg
│   ├── chicken-dish.jpg
│   ├── fried-rice.jpg
│   └── screenshot.png
├── LICENSE             # MIT License
└── README.md           # Documentation
```

## Setup & Deployment

### Local Development
1. Clone repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/sharon-portfolio.git
   ```

2. Navigate to project:
   ```bash
   cd sharon-portfolio
   ```

3. Open in browser:
   ```bash
   open index.html  # Mac
   start index.html # Windows
   ```

### Web Hosting
1. Upload all files to your hosting provider
2. Ensure all file paths are correct
3. Test all navigation links

## Customization Guide

1. **Personal Information**:
   - Update content in HTML files
   - Replace placeholder images
   - Modify contact details

2. **Styling**:
   - Color scheme: Edit CSS variables
   ```css
   :root {
     --primary: #2c3e50;
     --secondary: #e74c3c;
   }
   ```
   - Fonts: Change in `style.css`
   - Layout: Adjust container sizes

3. **Adding Content**:
   - New pages: Create HTML files and link in navigation
   - Recipes: Add to menu.html with proper linking
   - Research: Create new project entries

